The paper introduces a method for off-policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of structural causal models (SCMs) is a common approach in causal inference and machine learning, which suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (machine learning). The application of the method in high-risk settings such as healthcare suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science) or cs.CR (cryptography and security). Finally, the use of partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.SY (systems and control).
